Apache HTTP Server on LXC

1. single container
Make apache:
$ ./mk_apache <container name>
Start container and apache:
$ ./start_apache <container name>
Test apache with ab:
$ ./test_apache <container name>

2. batch testing
This will install apache on test1 to testn:
$ ./batch_mk_apache <numbere of instance>
This will start-test-stop apache on test1 to testn:
$ ./batch_test_apache <number of instance>

Note: all container_* scripts are used to be executed inside the container, do not execute in host.

